        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 3:42PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 342 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Organ Cave, or near Ronceverte, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Alleghany...
White Sulphur Springs...
Ronceverte...
Sweet Springs...
Fairlea...
Roaring Mountain Summit...
and Glace.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
